{"type":"message","id":"32534aab","parentId":"98ce0d00","timestamp":"2026-03-03T09:07:52.354Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7grsd6x8mdkt_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"query\":\"finnhub market news sentiment score popularity\",\"total\":5,\"results\":[{\"tool_id\":\"eodhd.sentiments.retrieve.v1.c2c27d35\",\"name\":\"Retrieve Sentiment Data\",\"description\":\"Get sentiment scores for one or more financial instruments (stocks, ETFs, crypto) calculated from news and social media, normalized on a scale from -1 (very negative) to 1 (very positive).\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"s\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"One or more comma-separated tickers, for example: AAPL.US,BTC-USD.CC\"}},{\"name\":\"from\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Start date for filtering sentiment data (YYYY-MM-DD)\"}},{\"name\":\"to\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"End date for filtering sentiment data (YYYY-MM-DD)\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"s\":\"AAPL.US,BTC-USD.CC\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Access historical end-of-day stock prices, intraday data, US stock options, and real-time prices with free and advanced plans. EODHD provides financial data for 150,000+ tickers, including stocks, ETFs, funds, and currencies worldwide.\",\"stats\":{\"avg_execution_time_ms\":1278.53,\"success_rate\":0.999}},{\"tool_id\":\"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.7aca3c4a\",\"name\":\"Market News & Sentiment\",\"description\":\"Returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from global news outlets covering stocks, crypto, forex, and economic topics.\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"function\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The function to call. In this case, NEWS_SENTIMENT\"},\"enum\":[\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"]},{\"name\":\"tickers\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Comma-separated list of stock/crypto/forex symbols to filter articles by (e.g., AAPL,CRYPTO:BTC).\"}},{\"name\":\"topics\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Comma-separated list of topics to filter by.\"},\"enum\":[\"blockchain\",\"earnings\",\"ipo\",\"mergers_and_acquisitions\",\"financial_markets\",\"economy_fiscal\",\"economy_monetary\",\"economy_macro\",\"energy_transportation\",\"finance\",\"life_sciences\",\"manufacturing\",\"real_estate\",\"retail_wholesale\",\"technology\"]},{\"name\":\"time_from\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Start time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format (e.g., 20220410T0130).\"}},{\"name\":\"time_to\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"End time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"}},{\"name\":\"sort\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Sorting method for results.\"},\"enum\":[\"LATEST\",\"EARLIEST\",\"RELEVANCE\"]},{\"name\":\"limit\",\"type\":\"integer\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Maximum number of results (up to 1000).\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"function\":\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\"stats\":{\"avg_execution_time_ms\":520.43,\"success_rate\":0.987}},{\"tool_id\":\"alphavantage.news_sentiment.retrieve.v1.7aca3c4a\",\"name\":\"Retrieve Market News & Sentiment\",\"description\":\"Returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from premier news outlets around the world, covering stocks, cryptocurrencies, forex, and various financial topics.\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"function\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The function name.\"},\"enum\":[\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"]},{\"name\":\"tickers\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Comma-separated list of stock/crypto/forex symbols (e.g., COIN,CRYPTO:BTC,FOREX:USD). Filters articles that mention all listed tickers.\"}},{\"name\":\"topics\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Comma-separated list of topics. Articles must cover all listed topics.\"},\"enum\":[\"blockchain\",\"earnings\",\"ipo\",\"mergers_and_acquisitions\",\"financial_markets\",\"economy_fiscal\",\"economy_monetary\",\"economy_macro\",\"energy_transportation\",\"finance\",\"life_sciences\",\"manufacturing\",\"real_estate\",\"retail_wholesale\",\"technology\"]},{\"name\":\"time_from\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Start time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format (e.g., 20220410T0130).\"}},{\"name\":\"time_to\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"End time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"}},{\"name\":\"sort\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Sorting method.\"},\"enum\":[\"LATEST\",\"EARLIEST\",\"RELEVANCE\"]},{\"name\":\"limit\",\"type\":\"integer\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Maximum number of results (up to 1000).\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"function\":\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\"stats\":{\"avg_execution_time_ms\":660.49,\"success_rate\":0.973}},{\"tool_id\":\"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.467a92c0\",\"name\":\"Market News & Sentiment Trending\",\"description\":\"This API returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from a large & growing selection of premier news outlets around the world, covering stocks, cryptocurrencies, forex, and a wide range of topics such as fiscal policy, mergers & acquisitions, IPOs, etc.\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"function\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The function of your choice. In this case, function=NEWS_SENTIMENT\"},\"enum\":[\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"]},{\"name\":\"tickers\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The stock/crypto/forex symbols of your choice. For example: tickers=IBM will filter for articles that mention the IBM ticker; tickers=COIN,CRYPTO:BTC,FOREX:USD will filter for articles that simultaneously mention Coinbase (COIN), Bitcoin (CRYPTO:BTC), and US Dollar (FOREX:USD) in their content.\"}},{\"name\":\"topics\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The news topics of your choice. For example: topics=technology will filter for articles that write about the technology sector; topics=technology,ipo will filter for articles that simultaneously cover technology and IPO in their content. Below is the full list of supported topics: Blockchain: blockchain, Earnings: earnings, IPO: ipo, Mergers & Acquisitions: mergers_and_acquisitions, Financial Markets: financial_markets, Economy - Fiscal Policy (e.g., tax reform, government spending): economy_fiscal, Economy - Monetary Policy (e.g., interest rates, inflation): economy_monetary, Economy - Macro/Overall: economy_macro, Energy & Transportation: energy_transportation, Finance: finance, Life Sciences: life_sciences, Manufacturing: manufacturing, Real Estate & Construction: real_estate, Retail & Wholesale: retail_wholesale, Technology: technology.\"}},{\"name\":\"time_from\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The time range of the news articles you are targeting, in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format. For example: time_from=20220410T0130. If time_from is specified but time_to is missing, the API will return articles published between the time_from value and the current time.\"}},{\"name\":\"time_to\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The time range of the news articles you are targeting, in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"}},{\"name\":\"sort\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"By default, sort=LATEST and the API will return the latest articles first. You can also set sort=EARLIEST or sort=RELEVANCE based on your use case.\"},\"enum\":[\"LATEST\",\"EARLIEST\",\"RELEVANCE\"]},{\"name\":\"limit\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"By default, limit=50 and the API will return up to 50 matching results. You can also set limit=1000 to output up to 1000 results.\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"function\":\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\"stats\":{\"avg_execution_time_ms\":883.34,\"success_rate\":0.946}},{\"tool_id\":\"finnhub.news.retrieve.v1.2e72ea5d\",\"name\":\"Market News\",\"description\":\"Get latest market news.\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"category\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"This parameter can be 1 of the following values <code>general, forex, crypto, merger</code>.\"}},{\"name\":\"minId\",\"type\":\"integer\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Use this field to get only news after this ID. Default to 0\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"category\":\"general\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Finnhub - Free APIs for realtime stock, forex, and cryptocurrency. Company fundamentals, Economic data, and Alternative data.\"}],\"search_id\":\"39713050-1f00-4b66-9365-425e1f2443c3\",\"elapsed_time_ms\":415.32}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3517,"aggregated":"{\"query\":\"finnhub market news sentiment score popularity\",\"total\":5,\"results\":[{\"tool_id\":\"eodhd.sentiments.retrieve.v1.c2c27d35\",\"name\":\"Retrieve Sentiment Data\",\"description\":\"Get sentiment scores for one or more financial instruments (stocks, ETFs, crypto) calculated from news and social media, normalized on a scale from -1 (very negative) to 1 (very positive).\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"s\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"One or more comma-separated tickers, for example: AAPL.US,BTC-USD.CC\"}},{\"name\":\"from\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Start date for filtering sentiment data (YYYY-MM-DD)\"}},{\"name\":\"to\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"End date for filtering sentiment data (YYYY-MM-DD)\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"s\":\"AAPL.US,BTC-USD.CC\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Access historical end-of-day stock prices, intraday data, US stock options, and real-time prices with free and advanced plans. EODHD provides financial data for 150,000+ tickers, including stocks, ETFs, funds, and currencies worldwide.\",\"stats\":{\"avg_execution_time_ms\":1278.53,\"success_rate\":0.999}},{\"tool_id\":\"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.7aca3c4a\",\"name\":\"Market News & Sentiment\",\"description\":\"Returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from global news outlets covering stocks, crypto, forex, and economic topics.\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"function\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The function to call. In this case, NEWS_SENTIMENT\"},\"enum\":[\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"]},{\"name\":\"tickers\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Comma-separated list of stock/crypto/forex symbols to filter articles by (e.g., AAPL,CRYPTO:BTC).\"}},{\"name\":\"topics\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Comma-separated list of topics to filter by.\"},\"enum\":[\"blockchain\",\"earnings\",\"ipo\",\"mergers_and_acquisitions\",\"financial_markets\",\"economy_fiscal\",\"economy_monetary\",\"economy_macro\",\"energy_transportation\",\"finance\",\"life_sciences\",\"manufacturing\",\"real_estate\",\"retail_wholesale\",\"technology\"]},{\"name\":\"time_from\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Start time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format (e.g., 20220410T0130).\"}},{\"name\":\"time_to\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"End time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"}},{\"name\":\"sort\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Sorting method for results.\"},\"enum\":[\"LATEST\",\"EARLIEST\",\"RELEVANCE\"]},{\"name\":\"limit\",\"type\":\"integer\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Maximum number of results (up to 1000).\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"function\":\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\"stats\":{\"avg_execution_time_ms\":520.43,\"success_rate\":0.987}},{\"tool_id\":\"alphavantage.news_sentiment.retrieve.v1.7aca3c4a\",\"name\":\"Retrieve Market News & Sentiment\",\"description\":\"Returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from premier news outlets around the world, covering stocks, cryptocurrencies, forex, and various financial topics.\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"function\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The function name.\"},\"enum\":[\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"]},{\"name\":\"tickers\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Comma-separated list of stock/crypto/forex symbols (e.g., COIN,CRYPTO:BTC,FOREX:USD). Filters articles that mention all listed tickers.\"}},{\"name\":\"topics\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Comma-separated list of topics. Articles must cover all listed topics.\"},\"enum\":[\"blockchain\",\"earnings\",\"ipo\",\"mergers_and_acquisitions\",\"financial_markets\",\"economy_fiscal\",\"economy_monetary\",\"economy_macro\",\"energy_transportation\",\"finance\",\"life_sciences\",\"manufacturing\",\"real_estate\",\"retail_wholesale\",\"technology\"]},{\"name\":\"time_from\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Start time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format (e.g., 20220410T0130).\"}},{\"name\":\"time_to\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"End time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"}},{\"name\":\"sort\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Sorting method.\"},\"enum\":[\"LATEST\",\"EARLIEST\",\"RELEVANCE\"]},{\"name\":\"limit\",\"type\":\"integer\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Maximum number of results (up to 1000).\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"function\":\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\"stats\":{\"avg_execution_time_ms\":660.49,\"success_rate\":0.973}},{\"tool_id\":\"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.467a92c0\",\"name\":\"Market News & Sentiment Trending\",\"description\":\"This API returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from a large & growing selection of premier news outlets around the world, covering stocks, cryptocurrencies, forex, and a wide range of topics such as fiscal policy, mergers & acquisitions, IPOs, etc.\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"function\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The function of your choice. In this case, function=NEWS_SENTIMENT\"},\"enum\":[\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"]},{\"name\":\"tickers\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The stock/crypto/forex symbols of your choice. For example: tickers=IBM will filter for articles that mention the IBM ticker; tickers=COIN,CRYPTO:BTC,FOREX:USD will filter for articles that simultaneously mention Coinbase (COIN), Bitcoin (CRYPTO:BTC), and US Dollar (FOREX:USD) in their content.\"}},{\"name\":\"topics\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The news topics of your choice. For example: topics=technology will filter for articles that write about the technology sector; topics=technology,ipo will filter for articles that simultaneously cover technology and IPO in their content. Below is the full list of supported topics: Blockchain: blockchain, Earnings: earnings, IPO: ipo, Mergers & Acquisitions: mergers_and_acquisitions, Financial Markets: financial_markets, Economy - Fiscal Policy (e.g., tax reform, government spending): economy_fiscal, Economy - Monetary Policy (e.g., interest rates, inflation): economy_monetary, Economy - Macro/Overall: economy_macro, Energy & Transportation: energy_transportation, Finance: finance, Life Sciences: life_sciences, Manufacturing: manufacturing, Real Estate & Construction: real_estate, Retail & Wholesale: retail_wholesale, Technology: technology.\"}},{\"name\":\"time_from\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The time range of the news articles you are targeting, in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format. For example: time_from=20220410T0130. If time_from is specified but time_to is missing, the API will return articles published between the time_from value and the current time.\"}},{\"name\":\"time_to\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"The time range of the news articles you are targeting, in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"}},{\"name\":\"sort\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"By default, sort=LATEST and the API will return the latest articles first. You can also set sort=EARLIEST or sort=RELEVANCE based on your use case.\"},\"enum\":[\"LATEST\",\"EARLIEST\",\"RELEVANCE\"]},{\"name\":\"limit\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"By default, limit=50 and the API will return up to 50 matching results. You can also set limit=1000 to output up to 1000 results.\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"function\":\"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\"stats\":{\"avg_execution_time_ms\":883.34,\"success_rate\":0.946}},{\"tool_id\":\"finnhub.news.retrieve.v1.2e72ea5d\",\"name\":\"Market News\",\"description\":\"Get latest market news.\",\"params\":[{\"name\":\"category\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true,\"description\":{\"en\":\"This parameter can be 1 of the following values <code>general, forex, crypto, merger</code>.\"}},{\"name\":\"minId\",\"type\":\"integer\",\"required\":false,\"description\":{\"en\":\"Use this field to get only news after this ID. Default to 0\"}}],\"examples\":{\"sample_parameters\":{\"category\":\"general\"}},\"provider_description\":\"Finnhub - Free APIs for realtime stock, forex, and cryptocurrency. Company fundamentals, Economic data, and Alternative data.\"}],\"search_id\":\"39713050-1f00-4b66-9365-425e1f2443c3\",\"elapsed_time_ms\":415.32}","cwd":"/Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772528872350}}
{"type":"message","id":"278f4070","parentId":"32534aab","timestamp":"2026-03-03T09:08:01.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"我注意到搜索结果中有`finnhub.news.retrieve.v1.2e72ea5d`这个工具，但执行时遇到了参数问题。\n\n让我仔细看看：当前获取的新闻数据包含`sentiment`数据，其中有`polarity`分数（-1到1之间）。也许用户说的\"热度80\"是指将polarity转换为0-100的分数？\n\n或者，也许Finnhub API本身有一个专门的\"热度\"字段。让我尝试使用不同的搜索，看看是否能找到原生的Finnhub新闻API。\n\n让我再看一下数据返回的具体内容。返回的JSON数据中有一个完整的新闻列表。让我查看是否有一条新闻有\"relevance\"或\"score\"字段。\n\n从之前的返回内容看，字段包括：date, title, content, link, symbols, tags, sentiment。sentiment里是polarity, neg, neu, pos。\n\n所以目前EODHD的API没有\"热度\"字段。但也许Alpha Vantage的NEWS_SENTIMENT有不同的字段。让我用sort=RELEVANCE来获取，看看是否会返回不同的数据：","thinkingSignature":"da2ec149ead00510d10d9282c88b6ce260cd86a8f7a9ceaf34d30172500fdab8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bdwgeenr6lbq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --connect-timeout 8 -m 30 -X POST https://qveris.ai/api/v1/tools/execute \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $QVERIS_API_KEY\" \\\n  -d '{\"tool_id\": \"eodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c\", \"params\": {\"limit\": 50, \"t\": \"technology\"}}'","timeout":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":30298,"output":343,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44625,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772528872354}}
{"type":"message","id":"7d85a45c","parentId":"278f4070","timestamp":"2026-03-03T09:08:09.543Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bdwgeenr6lbq_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"execution_id\":\"914a53af-a7a7-4326-b076-4c5cb855a167\",\"result\":{\"status_code\":200,\"message\":\"Result content is too long (235267 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\"full_content_file_url\":\"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260303%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2F3ced3a9cea8b4fc08482a3913a3f8357.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772536085&Signature=oN0Cksikx5MVUPJzeZqjT5jnK60%3D\",\"truncated_content\":\"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T08:37:08+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"LIVE: Rachel Reeves to deliver spring statement\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Rachel Reeves will tell MPs on Tuesday that the government has the “right economic plan for our country” as she delivers her spring statement against a backdrop of weaker growth forecasts and persistent global uncertainty.\\\\n\\\\nThe chancellor is expected to argue that the UK economy is “stronger and more secure” as a result of decisions already taken by ministers, pointing to easing inflation and lower borrowing costs as evidence that household pressures are beginning to abate.\\\\n\\\\nSpeaking in the Commons around noon on Tuesday, Reeves will say: “This government has the right economic plan for our country… in a world that has become yet more uncertain.\\\\n\\\\n“Stability in the public finances, investment in infrastructure and reform to our economy.\\\\n\\\\n“Building growth not on the contribution of a few people or a few parts of the country, but in every part of Britain with a state that doesn’t stand back, but steps up.”\\\\n\\\\nRead more: What to expect from Rachel Reeves' spring statement\\\\n\\\\nShe will add: “Because of the decisions we have already taken, we have a stronger and more secure economy. Inflation and interest rates [are] falling. And in every part of Britain, working people are better off.”\\\\n\\\\nHer remarks come weeks after the Bank of England cut its UK growth forecasts. In early February, the BoE downgraded its projection for gross domestic product growth in 2026 to 0.9% from 1.2%, and to 1.5% from 1.6% in 2027, underscoring the fragile outlook facing the government.\\\\n\\\\nMinisters have sought to play down expectations for the spring statement, insisting it will not contain new tax or spending measures. The government has committed to holding a single annual fiscal event, the autumn budget, at which major policy decisions on tax and spending will be set out.\\\\n\\\\nInstead, the spring statement will focus on responding to the Office for Budget Responsibility's (OBR) latest economic and fiscal forecasts.LIVE4 updates\\\\n\\\\n2 mins ago\\\\n\\\\nPedro Goncalves\\\\n\\\\nWhy is the spring statement important?\\\\n\\\\nRachel Reeves will use her spring statement to outline the latest economic forecasts from the Office for Budget Responsibility, which will be published shortly after she finishes speaking.\\\\n\\\\nDespite ministers billing the event as low-key, it is a significant moment. The updated projections will offer the clearest indication yet of the impact of the autumn budget and the government’s broader economic strategy.\\\\n\\\\nThe Office for Budget Responsibility produces two sets of forecasts each year, assessing the outlook for growth and the public finances and judging whether the government is on course to meet its self-imposed tax and spending rules.\\\\n\\\\nReeves has set two fiscal rules: not to borrow to fund day-to-day public spending by the end of this parliament, and to ensure that government debt is falling as a share of national income by the end of the parliament.\\\\n\\\\nThe watchdog was thrust into the spotlight at the November budget when it accidentally published its assessment about 40 minutes before the chancellor rose in the Commons, effectively revealing key elements of her plans in advance. 18 mins ago\\\\n\\\\nPedro Goncalves\\\\n\\\\nSpring statement overshadowed by oil surge and stagflation warnings\\\\n\\\\nDisruption to gas supplies in the Middle East poses a challenge for Britain, despite Qatar accounting for less than 2% of UK imports in 2024, owing to its impact on wholesale prices.\\\\n\\\\nBrent crude, the international benchmark, climbed back above $80 a barrel overnight, with some analysts warning that prices could reach $100 if the conflict persists.\\\\n\\\\nA renewed energy shock risks driving inflation higher, eroding consumer purchasing power, threatening growth and undermining Labour’s pledge to tackle the cost of living.\\\\n\\\\nAs economists at Investec explain: “The main economic consequence of higher energy prices would be to boost inflation.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"In the UK, illustratively, the current level of the oil price would, if maintained, add about 0.2%pts to headline inflation via higher petrol prices; and a sustained 40% shift up in natural gas price futures would boost this by a further 0.7%pts or so, via higher household utility bills.”\\\\n\\\\nAnalysts at DBS said the conflict raises “the spectre of stagflation”.\\\\n\\\\n“While energy prices are nowhere close to the levels seen during the start of the Russia-Ukraine conflict in 2022, investors will probably be keeping a close eye on the extent and duration that energy supplies will be disrupted,” they said. 22 mins ago\\\\n\\\\nPedro Goncalves\\\\n\\\\nChancellor has £22bn fiscal headroom\\\\n\\\\nIn her November Budget, Reeves built £21.7bn of headroom against her fiscal rules, a move that helped reassure bond markets. Since the 2024 election she has raised taxes by £66bn in an effort to restore fiscal stability.\\\\n\\\\nAlthough the chancellor retains a reserve to cushion households from higher energy costs later in the year if required, the Treasury says average household bills will fall by £117 from April and remain at that level for the following three months. 23 mins ago\\\\n\\\\nPedro Goncalves\\\\n\\\\nDon't expect new policies or tax changes, says Treasury\\\\n\\\\nRachel Reeves has pledged to hold only one fiscal event each year, the autumn budget, and will use Tuesday’s spring statement to deliver a brief address of about 20 minutes setting out updated forecasts from the Office for Budget Responsibility, the independent fiscal watchdog.\\\\n\\\\nTreasury officials said the chancellor would not announce new policies or tax changes and would adopt a “confident” tone on the UK economy's outlook.\\\\n\\\\nReeves is expected to postpone dealing with mounting pressures, including rising unemployment and a substantial shortfall in defence spending. Measures aimed at lifting the UK’s sluggish growth rate are due to be outlined in a separate speech later in March.\\\\n\\\\nDownload the Yahoo Finance app, available for Apple andAndroid.\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/live-rachel-reeves-spring-statement-083708130.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"FTSE.INDX\\\", \\\"GBPEUR.FOREX\\\", \\\"GBPUSD.FOREX\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ECONOMIC-FORECASTS\\\", \\\"ENERGY\\\", \\\"FISCAL-POLICY\\\", \\\"GROWTH RATE\\\", \\\"INFLATION\\\", \\\"STAGFLATION\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.967, \\\"neg\\\": 0.075, \\\"neu\\\": 0.826, \\\"pos\\\": 0.099}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T08:13:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Hogan Lovells Partners with LawFairy to Launch Legal Intelligence System Supporting Undocumented Children's Immigration Cases\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"LONDON, March  03, 2026  (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Hogan Lovells, a leading global law firm, has partnered with LawFairy, a legal intelligence company that automates complex legal and compliance workflows, to develop a structured, natural language immigration decision support system. This system, developed by LawFairy, will assist KIND UK in analysing an undocumented child's eligibility for registration as a British national, and in generating clear, consistent outputs to support triage and next steps. This is an area where Legal Aid is generally unavailable and where private representation is often unaffordable for some of the most vulnerable clients.\\\\n\\\\nCentral England Law Centre, one of the members of the KIND network in the UK partnering with Hogan Lovells, also collaborated with LawFairy on this initiative.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"An intake handling and decision support system like LawFairy will expand the sector's ability to handle many more requests for advice, despite the continuing collapse in numbers of qualified advisors in this area since 2010. Working with Hogan Lovells and LawFairy from the outset has enabled us to support LawFairy in the development of its legal technology platform to increase access to justice for people in need, bringing some of the benefits that the commercial legal world has already seen through automation into a sector which otherwise struggles to find private investment,\\\\\\\" said John Glanville, Project Coordinator for CELC.\\\\n\\\\nIn the UK, there are approximately 215,000 undocumented children, many of whom face significant barriers to accessing their rights. With the launch of this system, the legal sector will be able to enhance its capacity to help children navigate the complex immigration rules.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"It is incredible to see legal technology being used in this way to effect real change and have such an important and remarkable impact on an area of law which is in desperate need of being streamlined and simplified,\\\\\\\" said Michael O'Donoghue, Senior Associate, Hogan Lovells.\\\\n\\\\nThis system helps legal service providers navigate the fast-changing and complex area of immigration law and streamlines how support and advice are provided to applicants.\\\\n\\\\nThe platform works by:\\\\n\\\\nAsking the applicant a structured series of questions in plain English;Identifying potential application routes and flagging where specialist legal advice is needed; andProducing a clear report that can be used to triage cases and determine the most appropriate next steps.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"We are thrilled to partner with Hogan Lovells and CELC as a member of KIND in the UK on this vital initiative. At LawFairy, we are applying structured, explainable legal intelligence to help organisations deliver better outcomes at scale. Our mission is profit with purpose, and this new system exemplifies our commitment to supporting vulnerable communities. By making legal processes more accessible, efficient and easier to understand, we want to help ensure that every undocumented child has a fair chance to secure their rights and a brighter future,\\\\\\\" said Raj S. Panasar, Founder of LawFairy.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"We are seeing the exponential rise of use of legal technology in commercial environments but many of these developments are not available for the marginalised communities who are frequently missed out making access to justice even more remote. Working with the ingenuity and commitment of LawFairy over many years to perfect a workable, intelligent system which complements the empathetic immigration expertise of Central England Law Centres has been a challenge but also hugely rewarding. Also having the support of our global partner KIND has been incredibly important to allow us to reach into communities and gives us the potential to broaden access further. Above all this is an excellent demonstration of how collaboration for impact works!\\\\\\\" said Yasmin Waljee OBE, Partner, Hogan Lovells.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"As a charitable partnership, we're always looking for ways to improve our efficiency and scalability, while ensuring quality legal assistance to children and young people who need it most. Our partner, Central England Law Centre, worked with LawFairy to embed the knowledge, skill, and experience of specialist immigration lawyers into a system to support early evaluation of referrals, training and casework support, to quickly and confidently match the people who turn to us for help, to receive appropriate support and legal advice. We look forward to working with LawFairy to help us expand our ability to help more children and young people access their right to British nationality,\\\\\\\" a KIND spokesperson said.\\\\n\\\\nLawFairy has recently received authorisation from the Solicitors Regulation Authority (SRA) to operate as a law firm. It is believed to be the first technology-only firm in England and Wales built around a fully deterministic legal model.\\\\n\\\\nAbout LawFairy\\\\n\\\\nLawFairy is a legal intelligence company that builds structured, explainable systems to support complex legal and compliance decision-making. Its technology embeds legal expertise into clear, auditable workflows, helping organisations deliver defensible outcomes at scale while improving access to justice.\\\\n\\\\nAbout Hogan Lovells\\\\n\\\\nHogan Lovells is a leading global law firm with more than 2,800 lawyers across the world. The firm has a strong commitment to pro bono work and access to justice, using legal expertise and innovation to address unmet legal needs.\\\\n\\\\nAbout Central England Law Centre (CELC)\\\\n\\\\nCentral England Law Centre (CELC) is a charity providing specialist legal advice and representation to fight inequality. It advocates for people, challenges unfair decisions, takes cases to the highest courts and works in partnership with other support services and organisations. It operates in Coventry and Birmingham.\\\\n\\\\nCELC is also a member of the Law Centres Network, an alliance of 42 individual Law Centres, which has been at the centre of a movement for social justice for almost fifty years. CELC partners with KIND in the UK.\\\\n\\\\nAbout KIND\\\\n\\\\nKIND (Kids in Need of Defense) is a global leader in the protection of children on the move, unaccompanied and separated children, and those without proper legal status. Launched in 2008, KIND works across the globe to champion a world in which every child's rights and well-being are protected as they seek safety.\\\\n\\\\nKIND began working in the UK in 2016, and partners with five expert organisations and over 1,000 lawyers from law firms and corporate legal partners to provide pro bono legal services for children.\\\\n\\\\nKIND's work in the UK reaches children across the country, and:\\\\n\\\\nWorks on approximately 500 cases per yearHas consistently achieved a 98 percent success rate in cases with an outcome\\\\n\\\\nLawFairy Media Contact:\\\\n\\\\nSebastian Jenks\\\\n\\\\nseb.jenks@lawfairy.com\\\\n\\\\n+447875545442\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/03/03/3248039/0/en/Hogan-Lovells-Partners-with-LawFairy-to-Launch-Legal-Intelligence-System-Supporting-Undocumented-Children-s-Immigration-Cases.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ACCESSTOJUSTICE\\\", \\\"AI\\\", \\\"AUTOMATION\\\", \\\"CHILDREN\\\", \\\"FUTUREOFLAW\\\", \\\"IMMIGRATION\\\", \\\"LAW\\\", \\\"LEGAL\\\", \\\"LEGALAID\\\", \\\"LEGALINTELLIGENCE\\\", \\\"LEGALTECH\\\", \\\"PARTNERSHIP\\\", \\\"PARTNERSHIPS\\\", \\\"PROBONO\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 1, \\\"neg\\\": 0.015, \\\"neu\\\": 0.73, \\\"pos\\\": 0.255}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T08:11:16+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Assessing Whether Adidas (XTRA:ADS) Looks Undervalued After Recent Share Price Weakness\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Find your next quality investment with Simply Wall St's easy and powerful screener, trusted by over 7 million individual investors worldwide.\\\\n\\\\nRecent performance snapshot for adidas (XTRA:ADS)\\\\n\\\\nWith no single headline event driving sentiment today, adidas (XTRA:ADS) sits in focus for investors weighing recent share performance, current earnings profile, and how its valuation metrics compare with underlying business results.\\\\n\\\\nSee our latest analysis for adidas.\\\\n\\\\nAt a share price of €151.35, adidas has seen short term momentum soften, with a 1 day share price return of 4.33% decline and a year to date share price return of 9.59% decline. The 1 year total shareholder return of 38.46% loss contrasts with a modest 3 year total shareholder return of 4.96% gain, which points to fading momentum after earlier recovery.\\\\n\\\\nIf this recent pullback has you thinking about where else growth stories could emerge, it might be a good moment to scan 99 top founder-led companies as potential new ideas for your watchlist.\\\\n\\\\nWith revenue of €24.7b, net income of €1.21b and an indicated intrinsic value and analyst target both above the current €151.35 share price, you have to ask: is this a genuine opportunity, or is the market already factoring in future growth?\\\\n\\\\nMost Popular Narrative: 31.4% Undervalued\\\\n\\\\nAt €151.35, the most followed narrative for adidas points to a fair value of about €220.75, creating a sizeable gap between current price and long term expectations.\\\\n\\\\nThe accelerating global health and fitness movement is driving strong demand for adidas' performance and athleisure product categories, as demonstrated by double digit growth in key segments like Running (+25%), Training (+20%), and Basketball, positioning the company for sustained volume expansion and recurring sales growth (impacts revenue and earnings).\\\\n\\\\nRead the complete narrative.\\\\n\\\\nWant to see how this story holds together beyond headlines? The fair value hinges on a blend of steady top line expansion, firmer margins and a future earnings multiple that assumes adidas keeps momentum in its core categories without stretching expectations too far. The full narrative spells out how those moving parts fit into that valuation path.\\\\n\\\\nResult: Fair Value of €220.75 (UNDERVALUED)\\\\n\\\\nHave a read of the narrative in full and understand what's behind the forecasts.\\\\n\\\\nHowever, this depends on adidas managing tariff driven cost pressures and keeping pace with tougher competition, especially if fashion trends or key franchises cool faster than expected.\\\\n\\\\nFind out about the key risks to this adidas narrative.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nNext Steps\\\\n\\\\nIf this mix of optimism and caution has you thinking twice, take a moment to review the numbers yourself and form your own stance. You can start with 3 key rewards.\\\\n\\\\nLooking for more investment ideas?\\\\n\\\\nIf adidas has you rethinking your portfolio, do not stop here, broaden your watchlist with other stock ideas that match the way you like to invest.\\\\n\\\\nHunt for potential upside by scanning 222 high quality undervalued stocks that might be trading at prices below what their fundamentals suggest. Strengthen your income stream by checking out 453 dividend fortresses that focus on generous, higher yielding payouts. Sleep easier at night by reviewing 311 resilient stocks with low risk scores that score well on resilience and overall risk profile.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include ADS.DE.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/assessing-whether-adidas-xtra-ads-081116053.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"ADDDF.US\\\", \\\"ADS.F\\\", \\\"ADS.XETRA\\\", \\\"ADS1.F\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ATHLEISURE\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"INTRINSIC VALUE\\\", \\\"NET INCOME\\\", \\\"SHARE PRICE\\\", \\\"SHAREHOLDER\\\", \\\"VALUATION\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.997, \\\"neg\\\": 0.028, \\\"neu\\\": 0.827, \\\"pos\\\": 0.145}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T08:10:55+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"A Look At International Flavors &amp; Fragrances (IFF) Valuation After Portfolio Sale And Sustainable Fragrance Expansion\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Track your investments for FREE with Simply Wall St, the portfolio command center trusted by over 7 million individual investors worldwide.\\\\n\\\\nWhy IFF’s recent moves matter for investors\\\\n\\\\nInternational Flavors & Fragrances (IFF) has been reshaping its business, completing the sale of soy crush, concentrates and lecithin operations to Bunge, while also pushing further into sustainable fragrance ingredients and capacity expansion in France.\\\\n\\\\nSee our latest analysis for International Flavors & Fragrances.\\\\n\\\\nThose portfolio moves and the push into sustainable fragrance ingredients come as the share price sits at US$80.75, with a 30-day share price return of 15.67% and a year-to-date share price return of 18.70%. The 5-year total shareholder return of 29.65% contrasts with the recent momentum.\\\\n\\\\nIf you are weighing what else could benefit from similar long term consumer trends, it might be worth scanning our screener of 19 top founder-led companies as potential next ideas.\\\\n\\\\nWith IFF reporting US$10.89b in revenue but a net loss of US$361m, and trading at US$80.75 with some recent share price momentum, is the current valuation leaving upside on the table, or is the market already pricing in future growth?\\\\n\\\\nMost Popular Narrative: 10.7% Undervalued\\\\n\\\\nInternational Flavors & Fragrances’ most followed narrative pegs fair value at $90.47, compared with the last close at $80.75, framing the current debate around upside potential.\\\\n\\\\nOngoing investments in R&D and capacity (especially in Health & Biosciences, Taste, and Specialty Fragrance Ingredients) are strengthening the company's innovation pipeline; management expects these initiatives to accelerate revenue and pro\",\"content_schema\":{\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"date\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"title\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"content\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"link\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"symbols\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"tags\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"sentiment\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"null\"},{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"polarity\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"neg\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"neu\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"pos\":{\"type\":\"number\"}},\"required\":[\"neg\",\"neu\",\"polarity\",\"pos\"]}]}},\"required\":[\"content\",\"date\",\"link\",\"sentiment\",\"symbols\",\"tags\",\"title\"]}}},\"success\":true,\"elapsed_time_ms\":1980.86,\"cost\":6.5}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8070,"aggregated":"{\"execution_id\":\"914a53af-a7a7-4326-b076-4c5cb855a167\",\"result\":{\"status_code\":200,\"message\":\"Result content is too long (235267 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\"full_content_file_url\":\"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260303%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2F3ced3a9cea8b4fc08482a3913a3f8357.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772536085&Signature=oN0Cksikx5MVUPJzeZqjT5jnK60%3D\",\"truncated_content\":\"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T08:37:08+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"LIVE: Rachel Reeves to deliver spring statement\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Rachel Reeves will tell MPs on Tuesday that the government has the “right economic plan for our country” as she delivers her spring statement against a backdrop of weaker growth forecasts and persistent global uncertainty.\\\\n\\\\nThe chancellor is expected to argue that the UK economy is “stronger and more secure” as a result of decisions already taken by ministers, pointing to easing inflation and lower borrowing costs as evidence that household pressures are beginning to abate.\\\\n\\\\nSpeaking in the Commons around noon on Tuesday, Reeves will say: “This government has the right economic plan for our country… in a world that has become yet more uncertain.\\\\n\\\\n“Stability in the public finances, investment in infrastructure and reform to our economy.\\\\n\\\\n“Building growth not on the contribution of a few people or a few parts of the country, but in every part of Britain with a state that doesn’t stand back, but steps up.”\\\\n\\\\nRead more: What to expect from Rachel Reeves' spring statement\\\\n\\\\nShe will add: “Because of the decisions we have already taken, we have a stronger and more secure economy. Inflation and interest rates [are] falling. And in every part of Britain, working people are better off.”\\\\n\\\\nHer remarks come weeks after the Bank of England cut its UK growth forecasts. In early February, the BoE downgraded its projection for gross domestic product growth in 2026 to 0.9% from 1.2%, and to 1.5% from 1.6% in 2027, underscoring the fragile outlook facing the government.\\\\n\\\\nMinisters have sought to play down expectations for the spring statement, insisting it will not contain new tax or spending measures. The government has committed to holding a single annual fiscal event, the autumn budget, at which major policy decisions on tax and spending will be set out.\\\\n\\\\nInstead, the spring statement will focus on responding to the Office for Budget Responsibility's (OBR) latest economic and fiscal forecasts.LIVE4 updates\\\\n\\\\n2 mins ago\\\\n\\\\nPedro Goncalves\\\\n\\\\nWhy is the spring statement important?\\\\n\\\\nRachel Reeves will use her spring statement to outline the latest economic forecasts from the Office for Budget Responsibility, which will be published shortly after she finishes speaking.\\\\n\\\\nDespite ministers billing the event as low-key, it is a significant moment. The updated projections will offer the clearest indication yet of the impact of the autumn budget and the government’s broader economic strategy.\\\\n\\\\nThe Office for Budget Responsibility produces two sets of forecasts each year, assessing the outlook for growth and the public finances and judging whether the government is on course to meet its self-imposed tax and spending rules.\\\\n\\\\nReeves has set two fiscal rules: not to borrow to fund day-to-day public spending by the end of this parliament, and to ensure that government debt is falling as a share of national income by the end of the parliament.\\\\n\\\\nThe watchdog was thrust into the spotlight at the November budget when it accidentally published its assessment about 40 minutes before the chancellor rose in the Commons, effectively revealing key elements of her plans in advance. 18 mins ago\\\\n\\\\nPedro Goncalves\\\\n\\\\nSpring statement overshadowed by oil surge and stagflation warnings\\\\n\\\\nDisruption to gas supplies in the Middle East poses a challenge for Britain, despite Qatar accounting for less than 2% of UK imports in 2024, owing to its impact on wholesale prices.\\\\n\\\\nBrent crude, the international benchmark, climbed back above $80 a barrel overnight, with some analysts warning that prices could reach $100 if the conflict persists.\\\\n\\\\nA renewed energy shock risks driving inflation higher, eroding consumer purchasing power, threatening growth and undermining Labour’s pledge to tackle the cost of living.\\\\n\\\\nAs economists at Investec explain: “The main economic consequence of higher energy prices would be to boost inflation.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"In the UK, illustratively, the current level of the oil price would, if maintained, add about 0.2%pts to headline inflation via higher petrol prices; and a sustained 40% shift up in natural gas price futures would boost this by a further 0.7%pts or so, via higher household utility bills.”\\\\n\\\\nAnalysts at DBS said the conflict raises “the spectre of stagflation”.\\\\n\\\\n“While energy prices are nowhere close to the levels seen during the start of the Russia-Ukraine conflict in 2022, investors will probably be keeping a close eye on the extent and duration that energy supplies will be disrupted,” they said. 22 mins ago\\\\n\\\\nPedro Goncalves\\\\n\\\\nChancellor has £22bn fiscal headroom\\\\n\\\\nIn her November Budget, Reeves built £21.7bn of headroom against her fiscal rules, a move that helped reassure bond markets. Since the 2024 election she has raised taxes by £66bn in an effort to restore fiscal stability.\\\\n\\\\nAlthough the chancellor retains a reserve to cushion households from higher energy costs later in the year if required, the Treasury says average household bills will fall by £117 from April and remain at that level for the following three months. 23 mins ago\\\\n\\\\nPedro Goncalves\\\\n\\\\nDon't expect new policies or tax changes, says Treasury\\\\n\\\\nRachel Reeves has pledged to hold only one fiscal event each year, the autumn budget, and will use Tuesday’s spring statement to deliver a brief address of about 20 minutes setting out updated forecasts from the Office for Budget Responsibility, the independent fiscal watchdog.\\\\n\\\\nTreasury officials said the chancellor would not announce new policies or tax changes and would adopt a “confident” tone on the UK economy's outlook.\\\\n\\\\nReeves is expected to postpone dealing with mounting pressures, including rising unemployment and a substantial shortfall in defence spending. Measures aimed at lifting the UK’s sluggish growth rate are due to be outlined in a separate speech later in March.\\\\n\\\\nDownload the Yahoo Finance app, available for Apple andAndroid.\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/live-rachel-reeves-spring-statement-083708130.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"FTSE.INDX\\\", \\\"GBPEUR.FOREX\\\", \\\"GBPUSD.FOREX\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ECONOMIC-FORECASTS\\\", \\\"ENERGY\\\", \\\"FISCAL-POLICY\\\", \\\"GROWTH RATE\\\", \\\"INFLATION\\\", \\\"STAGFLATION\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.967, \\\"neg\\\": 0.075, \\\"neu\\\": 0.826, \\\"pos\\\": 0.099}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T08:13:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Hogan Lovells Partners with LawFairy to Launch Legal Intelligence System Supporting Undocumented Children's Immigration Cases\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"LONDON, March  03, 2026  (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Hogan Lovells, a leading global law firm, has partnered with LawFairy, a legal intelligence company that automates complex legal and compliance workflows, to develop a structured, natural language immigration decision support system. This system, developed by LawFairy, will assist KIND UK in analysing an undocumented child's eligibility for registration as a British national, and in generating clear, consistent outputs to support triage and next steps. This is an area where Legal Aid is generally unavailable and where private representation is often unaffordable for some of the most vulnerable clients.\\\\n\\\\nCentral England Law Centre, one of the members of the KIND network in the UK partnering with Hogan Lovells, also collaborated with LawFairy on this initiative.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"An intake handling and decision support system like LawFairy will expand the sector's ability to handle many more requests for advice, despite the continuing collapse in numbers of qualified advisors in this area since 2010. Working with Hogan Lovells and LawFairy from the outset has enabled us to support LawFairy in the development of its legal technology platform to increase access to justice for people in need, bringing some of the benefits that the commercial legal world has already seen through automation into a sector which otherwise struggles to find private investment,\\\\\\\" said John Glanville, Project Coordinator for CELC.\\\\n\\\\nIn the UK, there are approximately 215,000 undocumented children, many of whom face significant barriers to accessing their rights. With the launch of this system, the legal sector will be able to enhance its capacity to help children navigate the complex immigration rules.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"It is incredible to see legal technology being used in this way to effect real change and have such an important and remarkable impact on an area of law which is in desperate need of being streamlined and simplified,\\\\\\\" said Michael O'Donoghue, Senior Associate, Hogan Lovells.\\\\n\\\\nThis system helps legal service providers navigate the fast-changing and complex area of immigration law and streamlines how support and advice are provided to applicants.\\\\n\\\\nThe platform works by:\\\\n\\\\nAsking the applicant a structured series of questions in plain English;Identifying potential application routes and flagging where specialist legal advice is needed; andProducing a clear report that can be used to triage cases and determine the most appropriate next steps.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"We are thrilled to partner with Hogan Lovells and CELC as a member of KIND in the UK on this vital initiative. At LawFairy, we are applying structured, explainable legal intelligence to help organisations deliver better outcomes at scale. Our mission is profit with purpose, and this new system exemplifies our commitment to supporting vulnerable communities. By making legal processes more accessible, efficient and easier to understand, we want to help ensure that every undocumented child has a fair chance to secure their rights and a brighter future,\\\\\\\" said Raj S. Panasar, Founder of LawFairy.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"We are seeing the exponential rise of use of legal technology in commercial environments but many of these developments are not available for the marginalised communities who are frequently missed out making access to justice even more remote. Working with the ingenuity and commitment of LawFairy over many years to perfect a workable, intelligent system which complements the empathetic immigration expertise of Central England Law Centres has been a challenge but also hugely rewarding. Also having the support of our global partner KIND has been incredibly important to allow us to reach into communities and gives us the potential to broaden access further. Above all this is an excellent demonstration of how collaboration for impact works!\\\\\\\" said Yasmin Waljee OBE, Partner, Hogan Lovells.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"As a charitable partnership, we're always looking for ways to improve our efficiency and scalability, while ensuring quality legal assistance to children and young people who need it most. Our partner, Central England Law Centre, worked with LawFairy to embed the knowledge, skill, and experience of specialist immigration lawyers into a system to support early evaluation of referrals, training and casework support, to quickly and confidently match the people who turn to us for help, to receive appropriate support and legal advice. We look forward to working with LawFairy to help us expand our ability to help more children and young people access their right to British nationality,\\\\\\\" a KIND spokesperson said.\\\\n\\\\nLawFairy has recently received authorisation from the Solicitors Regulation Authority (SRA) to operate as a law firm. It is believed to be the first technology-only firm in England and Wales built around a fully deterministic legal model.\\\\n\\\\nAbout LawFairy\\\\n\\\\nLawFairy is a legal intelligence company that builds structured, explainable systems to support complex legal and compliance decision-making. Its technology embeds legal expertise into clear, auditable workflows, helping organisations deliver defensible outcomes at scale while improving access to justice.\\\\n\\\\nAbout Hogan Lovells\\\\n\\\\nHogan Lovells is a leading global law firm with more than 2,800 lawyers across the world. The firm has a strong commitment to pro bono work and access to justice, using legal expertise and innovation to address unmet legal needs.\\\\n\\\\nAbout Central England Law Centre (CELC)\\\\n\\\\nCentral England Law Centre (CELC) is a charity providing specialist legal advice and representation to fight inequality. It advocates for people, challenges unfair decisions, takes cases to the highest courts and works in partnership with other support services and organisations. It operates in Coventry and Birmingham.\\\\n\\\\nCELC is also a member of the Law Centres Network, an alliance of 42 individual Law Centres, which has been at the centre of a movement for social justice for almost fifty years. CELC partners with KIND in the UK.\\\\n\\\\nAbout KIND\\\\n\\\\nKIND (Kids in Need of Defense) is a global leader in the protection of children on the move, unaccompanied and separated children, and those without proper legal status. Launched in 2008, KIND works across the globe to champion a world in which every child's rights and well-being are protected as they seek safety.\\\\n\\\\nKIND began working in the UK in 2016, and partners with five expert organisations and over 1,000 lawyers from law firms and corporate legal partners to provide pro bono legal services for children.\\\\n\\\\nKIND's work in the UK reaches children across the country, and:\\\\n\\\\nWorks on approximately 500 cases per yearHas consistently achieved a 98 percent success rate in cases with an outcome\\\\n\\\\nLawFairy Media Contact:\\\\n\\\\nSebastian Jenks\\\\n\\\\nseb.jenks@lawfairy.com\\\\n\\\\n+447875545442\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/03/03/3248039/0/en/Hogan-Lovells-Partners-with-LawFairy-to-Launch-Legal-Intelligence-System-Supporting-Undocumented-Children-s-Immigration-Cases.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ACCESSTOJUSTICE\\\", \\\"AI\\\", \\\"AUTOMATION\\\", \\\"CHILDREN\\\", \\\"FUTUREOFLAW\\\", \\\"IMMIGRATION\\\", \\\"LAW\\\", \\\"LEGAL\\\", \\\"LEGALAID\\\", \\\"LEGALINTELLIGENCE\\\", \\\"LEGALTECH\\\", \\\"PARTNERSHIP\\\", \\\"PARTNERSHIPS\\\", \\\"PROBONO\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 1, \\\"neg\\\": 0.015, \\\"neu\\\": 0.73, \\\"pos\\\": 0.255}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T08:11:16+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Assessing Whether Adidas (XTRA:ADS) Looks Undervalued After Recent Share Price Weakness\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Find your next quality investment with Simply Wall St's easy and powerful screener, trusted by over 7 million individual investors worldwide.\\\\n\\\\nRecent performance snapshot for adidas (XTRA:ADS)\\\\n\\\\nWith no single headline event driving sentiment today, adidas (XTRA:ADS) sits in focus for investors weighing recent share performance, current earnings profile, and how its valuation metrics compare with underlying business results.\\\\n\\\\nSee our latest analysis for adidas.\\\\n\\\\nAt a share price of €151.35, adidas has seen short term momentum soften, with a 1 day share price return of 4.33% decline and a year to date share price return of 9.59% decline. The 1 year total shareholder return of 38.46% loss contrasts with a modest 3 year total shareholder return of 4.96% gain, which points to fading momentum after earlier recovery.\\\\n\\\\nIf this recent pullback has you thinking about where else growth stories could emerge, it might be a good moment to scan 99 top founder-led companies as potential new ideas for your watchlist.\\\\n\\\\nWith revenue of €24.7b, net income of €1.21b and an indicated intrinsic value and analyst target both above the current €151.35 share price, you have to ask: is this a genuine opportunity, or is the market already factoring in future growth?\\\\n\\\\nMost Popular Narrative: 31.4% Undervalued\\\\n\\\\nAt €151.35, the most followed narrative for adidas points to a fair value of about €220.75, creating a sizeable gap between current price and long term expectations.\\\\n\\\\nThe accelerating global health and fitness movement is driving strong demand for adidas' performance and athleisure product categories, as demonstrated by double digit growth in key segments like Running (+25%), Training (+20%), and Basketball, positioning the company for sustained volume expansion and recurring sales growth (impacts revenue and earnings).\\\\n\\\\nRead the complete narrative.\\\\n\\\\nWant to see how this story holds together beyond headlines? The fair value hinges on a blend of steady top line expansion, firmer margins and a future earnings multiple that assumes adidas keeps momentum in its core categories without stretching expectations too far. The full narrative spells out how those moving parts fit into that valuation path.\\\\n\\\\nResult: Fair Value of €220.75 (UNDERVALUED)\\\\n\\\\nHave a read of the narrative in full and understand what's behind the forecasts.\\\\n\\\\nHowever, this depends on adidas managing tariff driven cost pressures and keeping pace with tougher competition, especially if fashion trends or key franchises cool faster than expected.\\\\n\\\\nFind out about the key risks to this adidas narrative.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nNext Steps\\\\n\\\\nIf this mix of optimism and caution has you thinking twice, take a moment to review the numbers yourself and form your own stance. You can start with 3 key rewards.\\\\n\\\\nLooking for more investment ideas?\\\\n\\\\nIf adidas has you rethinking your portfolio, do not stop here, broaden your watchlist with other stock ideas that match the way you like to invest.\\\\n\\\\nHunt for potential upside by scanning 222 high quality undervalued stocks that might be trading at prices below what their fundamentals suggest. Strengthen your income stream by checking out 453 dividend fortresses that focus on generous, higher yielding payouts. Sleep easier at night by reviewing 311 resilient stocks with low risk scores that score well on resilience and overall risk profile.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include ADS.DE.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/assessing-whether-adidas-xtra-ads-081116053.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"ADDDF.US\\\", \\\"ADS.F\\\", \\\"ADS.XETRA\\\", \\\"ADS1.F\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ATHLEISURE\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"INTRINSIC VALUE\\\", \\\"NET INCOME\\\", \\\"SHARE PRICE\\\", \\\"SHAREHOLDER\\\", \\\"VALUATION\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.997, \\\"neg\\\": 0.028, \\\"neu\\\": 0.827, \\\"pos\\\": 0.145}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T08:10:55+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"A Look At International Flavors &amp; Fragrances (IFF) Valuation After Portfolio Sale And Sustainable Fragrance Expansion\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Track your investments for FREE with Simply Wall St, the portfolio command center trusted by over 7 million individual investors worldwide.\\\\n\\\\nWhy IFF’s recent moves matter for investors\\\\n\\\\nInternational Flavors & Fragrances (IFF) has been reshaping its business, completing the sale of soy crush, concentrates and lecithin operations to Bunge, while also pushing further into sustainable fragrance ingredients and capacity expansion in France.\\\\n\\\\nSee our latest analysis for International Flavors & Fragrances.\\\\n\\\\nThose portfolio moves and the push into sustainable fragrance ingredients come as the share price sits at US$80.75, with a 30-day share price return of 15.67% and a year-to-date share price return of 18.70%. The 5-year total shareholder return of 29.65% contrasts with the recent momentum.\\\\n\\\\nIf you are weighing what else could benefit from similar long term consumer trends, it might be worth scanning our screener of 19 top founder-led companies as potential next ideas.\\\\n\\\\nWith IFF reporting US$10.89b in revenue but a net loss of US$361m, and trading at US$80.75 with some recent share price momentum, is the current valuation leaving upside on the table, or is the market already pricing in future growth?\\\\n\\\\nMost Popular Narrative: 10.7% Undervalued\\\\n\\\\nInternational Flavors & Fragrances’ most followed narrative pegs fair value at $90.47, compared with the last close at $80.75, framing the current debate around upside potential.\\\\n\\\\nOngoing investments in R&D and capacity (especially in Health & Biosciences, Taste, and Specialty Fragrance Ingredients) are strengthening the company's innovation pipeline; management expects these initiatives to accelerate revenue and pro\",\"content_schema\":{\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"date\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"title\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"content\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"link\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"symbols\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"tags\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"sentiment\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"null\"},{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"polarity\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"neg\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"neu\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"pos\":{\"type\":\"number\"}},\"required\":[\"neg\",\"neu\",\"polarity\",\"pos\"]}]}},\"required\":[\"content\",\"date\",\"link\",\"sentiment\",\"symbols\",\"tags\",\"title\"]}}},\"success\":true,\"elapsed_time_ms\":1980.86,\"cost\":6.5}","cwd":"/Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772528889538}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7e367af","parentId":"7d85a45c","timestamp":"2026-03-03T09:08:25.415Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"我已经获取到了新闻数据。从数据来看，每条新闻都有一个\"sentiment\"字段，包含：\n- polarity: -1 到 1 之间的分数\n- neg, neu, pos: 负面、中性、正面的比例\n\n现在我需要找到一种方法来衡量\"热度\"。polarity值乘以100可以得到接近80的值。例如：\n- polarity 0.967 -> 96.7 (约97)\n- polarity 1.0 -> 100\n- polarity 0.997 -> 99.7 (约100)\n\n看起来这些polarity值非常高。如果用户的\"热度80\"是指polarity * 100，那么以下新闻可能符合条件：\n1. \"LIVE: Rachel Reeves to deliver spring statement\" - polarity: 0.967 → 热度 96.7\n2. \"Hogan Lovells Partners with LawFairy...\" - polarity: 1.0 → 热度 100\n3. \"Assessing Whether Adidas...\" - polarity: 0.997 → 热度 99.7\n\n让我获取更多新闻数据，看看有没有更多符合\"热度≥80\"条件的新闻。\n\n从截断的内容来看，我只能看到前4条新闻，让我获取更多数据，或者使用fetch获取完整的JSON文件来查看更多新闻：","thinkingSignature":"4c0b66178412932b7853c01dda539a510898ae210334b113f1601872828e6a78"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wfexa7y6sabs_1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"maxChars":30000,"url":"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260303%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2Fa483419a4eeb42f0b47dd1f79a4112a6.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":35676,"output":361,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50021,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772528889544}}
